Description: Body sherd of East Greek, probably Aeolian, grey ware pottery closed vessel, possibly an amphora or oinochoe; exterior: dark grey slip and inscription with traces of added red paint.
Curator's comments: There is a modern incised inscription 'Diosk' on interior indicates findspot. Red paint applied to the inscription can also be observed in a few other cases of grey ware at Naukratis. The fabric finds parallels with British Museum 1888,0601.637 which was analysed with NAA by Hans Mommsen (Bonn). The results placed the fabric (sample NAUK 64) in NAA group G and the origin was determined to be Aeolis.
Probably from same vase as British Museum 1965,0930.403 and 404, which also have a two-line inscription.
Bibliographic references: Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (pl. 22.3)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GL.155)
